reviewText: The DVD is a presentation of lessons for the little ones conveyed by likeable if not imperfect characters that learn from their own mistakes subsequently before being potentially committed by the juvenile viewer themselves. Disney needs to release more of these episodes ESPECIALLY the holiday shows which are beautiful examples of diverse celebrations around the world.

Special Agent Oso: License to Play is a 2014 Disney DVD compilation of mini-sodes of the popular Disney Junior animated series. Each mini-sode has a family-friendly alternate name for every James Bond movie title as Oso(Sean Astin, The Lord of the Rings Trilogy), an agent of U.N.I.Q.U.E. helps out everyday pre-schoolers learn new skills and Oso himself learns as well. The DVD includes sneak peeks of other Disney favourites. Like a trailer for DisneyNature's Monkey Kingdom, and a teaser trailer for the live-action version of Cinderella. Special Agent Oso: License to Play is a Disney treat for young viewers!

My girls (ages 4 and 7) love Special Agent Oso and we have a ton of the episodes on our DVR, including all of the episodes from this DVD. The show is great for its cute characters and fun problem solving. It always has a positive message and teaches kids about a variety of subjects through spy training exercises and special assignments. It also has clever James Bond references in all of the episode titles.

This DVD contains 12 great episodes. Amazon doesn't always do a good job on their DVD episode listings so here are the episodes that are included on this DVD:

1. Diamonds Are For Kites
2. Carousel Royale
3. Live And Jump Rope
4. Hopscotch Royale
5. Goldringer
6. License To Twirl
7. Hide Another Day
8. The Girl Who Cheered Me
9. A View To A Ball
10. Thunderbasket
11. Goldputter
12. Dr. Throw
